. // Toy data: show meta2p reproduces 1-stage Poisson
. 
. clear

. input study z d py

         study          z          d         py
  1. 1 0 40 1000 
  2. 1 1 10 1000
  3. 2 0 60 1000 
  4. 2 1 60 1000
  5. end

. poisson d z i.study, exp(py)

Iteration 0:  Log likelihood =   -17.7553  
Iteration 1:  Log likelihood = -17.755288  
Iteration 2:  Log likelihood = -17.755288  

Poisson regression                                      Number of obs =      4
                                                        LR chi2(2)    =  35.02
                                                        Prob > chi2   = 0.0000
Log likelihood = -17.755288                             Pseudo R2     = 0.4965

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
           d | Coefficient  Std. err.      z    P>|z|     [95% conf. interval]
-------------+----------------------------------------------------------------
           z |  -.3566749   .1558387    -2.29   0.022    -.6621133   -.0512366
     2.study |   .8754687   .1683251     5.20   0.000     .5455576     1.20538
       _cons |  -3.526361   .1552986   -22.71   0.000     -3.83074   -3.221981
      ln(py) |          1  (exposure)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

. local true = _b[z]

. local truese = _se[z]

. 
. gen lograte = log(d/py)

. gen var = 1/d

. reshape wide d py lograte var, i(study) j(z)
(j = 0 1)

Data                               Long   ->   Wide
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Number of observations                4   ->   2           
Number of variables                   6   ->   9           
j variable (2 values)                 z   ->   (dropped)
xij variables:
                                      d   ->   d0 d1
                                     py   ->   py0 py1
                                lograte   ->   lograte0 lograte1
                                    var   ->   var0 var1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

. gen est = lograte1-lograte0

. gen se = sqrt(var1+var0)

. metan est se, nograph model(fixed)

Studies included: 2
Participants included: Unknown

Meta-analysis pooling of aggregate data
using the common-effect inverse-variance model

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Study                |   Effect    [95% Conf. Interval]   % Weight
---------------------+----------------------------------------------
1                    |    -1.386     -2.079    -0.693      21.05
2                    |     0.000     -0.358     0.358      78.95
---------------------+----------------------------------------------
Overall, IV          |    -0.292     -0.610     0.026     100.00
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Test of overall effect = 0:  z =  -1.799  p = 0.072


Heterogeneity measures, calculated from the data
with Conf. Intervals based on non-central chi² (common-effect) distribution for Q
---------------------------------------------------------
Measure              |     Value      df      p-value
---------------------+-----------------------------------
Cochran's Q          |     12.14        1      0.000
                     |            -[95% Conf. Interval]-
H                    |     3.484     1.377     5.297
I² (%)               |     91.8%     47.3%     96.4%
---------------------------------------------------------
H = relative excess in Cochran's Q over its degrees-of-freedom
I² = proportion of total variation in effect estimate due to between-study heterogeneity (based on Q
> )

